  "texts": [
    "It shows the accuracy of the Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) used in this study.",
    "After the final training, the model was performing efficiently with a training accuracy of 96.76% and training loss of 0.0833 at the final epoch shows little amount of errors.",
    "The model was trained up to 200 epochs using a batch size of 2000, the training done with the help of the Adam optimizer and loss function of Sparse Categorical Cross entropy.",
    "An LSTM category of layers was incorporated into the model which consisted of two LSTM layers each with 20 units and a Dense category with 10 units.",
    "Such a design allowed the model to better capture and learn temporal structure in the data useful for sequence-based intrusion detection tasks."
  ],
